00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:15,537
Words said in friendship
with the best of intentions

296
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:21,282
always wind up hurting your friends deeply

297
00:40:21,886 --> 00:40:24,517
And then you wind up getting hurt

298
00:40:27,992 --> 00:40:30,486
Is friendship always that way?

299
00:40:31,095 --> 00:40:33,487
If that's so, what's left?

300
00:40:35,065 --> 00:40:37,263
If I were you...

301
00:40:42,873 --> 00:40:46,300
Who needs friends like that

302
00:40:47,111 --> 00:40:51,278
A courageous choice in itself

303
00:41:11,035 --> 00:41:13,563
Are you OK?

304
00:41:16,874 --> 00:41:20,267
Did something happen?

305
00:41:24,014 --> 00:41:27,316
If something happened, let's talk about it

306
00:41:35,125 --> 00:41:37,460
Both Junco and I,

307
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:40,388
are really worried

308
00:41:43,100 --> 00:41:45,298
I saw...

309
00:41:45,903 --> 00:41:47,430
A face...

310
00:41:47,905 --> 00:41:49,329
What?

311
00:41:49,940 --> 00:41:51,535
A horrible face...

312
00:41:55,012 --> 00:41:58,405
I've never seen anything like it...

313
00:41:58,983 --> 00:42:02,353
What are you saying? What did you see?

314
00:42:04,154 --> 00:42:06,022
The Forbidden Room

315
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:09,359
Forbidden Room? What's that?

316
00:42:13,964 --> 00:42:15,491
Is that...

317
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:18,562
The room with the red tape?

318
00:42:18,903 --> 00:42:20,498
Don't dare go in there!

319
00:42:26,143 --> 00:42:28,273
Please,

320
00:42:28,946 --> 00:42:30,439
tell me

321
00:42:31,181 --> 00:42:33,447
What happened?

322
00:42:42,059 --> 00:42:43,552
I'm cold

323
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:52,298
Yabe...

324
00:42:55,906 --> 00:42:57,433
Are you OK?

325
00:44:44,081 --> 00:44:47,315
Exit

326
00:45:28,926 --> 00:45:30,419
Harue

327
00:45:32,930 --> 00:45:34,354
Hi

328
00:45:37,167 --> 00:45:41,003
I don't really use the library much

329
00:45:41,004 --> 00:45:43,464
Couldn't find the way out

330
00:45:47,878 --> 00:45:50,304
Phantoms

331
00:45:52,116 --> 00:45:54,382
You reading this?

332
00:45:54,918 --> 00:45:56,342
Yeah

333
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:59,516
Is it related to your work in the lab?

334
00:46:02,025 --> 00:46:03,449
Yeah

335
00:46:03,994 --> 00:46:05,487
Huh...

336
00:46:08,966 --> 00:46:10,967
Do you have a minute?

337
00:46:10,968 --> 00:46:14,429
What? Sure

338
00:46:15,105 --> 00:46:17,269
Come

339
00:46:33,157 --> 00:46:35,526
Isn't it strange?

340
00:46:36,927 --> 00:46:39,421
Yeah... sort of...

341
00:46:49,072 --> 00:46:51,498
Almost like ghosts, right?

342
00:46:53,043 --> 00:46:56,345
You're right, they're like ghosts

343
00:46:59,016 --> 00:47:02,511
Sometimes, these turn up

344
00:47:03,053 --> 00:47:06,389
At first, they look like the other dots

345
00:47:07,958 --> 00:47:09,451
What are they?

346
00:47:10,060 --> 00:47:12,292
I don't know

347
00:47:13,897 --> 00:47:15,131
A bug?

348
00:47:15,132 --> 00:47:17,262
No

349
00:47:35,085 --> 00:47:37,119
That website...

350
00:47:37,120 --> 00:47:38,544
What?

351
00:47:39,923 --> 00:47:43,418
Oh, what happened with that?

352
00:47:43,894 --> 00:47:46,128
Nothing... yet...

353
00:47:46,129 --> 00:47:47,519
Huh...

354
00:47:47,931 --> 00:47:50,493
But I think they're related...

355
00:47:52,035 --> 00:47:55,405
I'm sure they're related

356
00:47:56,073 --> 00:47:58,271
You think?

357
00:48:10,153 --> 00:48:12,955
Let me know if anything happens

358
00:48:12,956 --> 00:48:14,483
Yeah, sure

359
00:48:23,934 --> 00:48:25,495
Karasawa san

360
00:48:26,003 --> 00:48:27,136
I need you to check this

361
00:48:27,137 --> 00:48:29,267
Yes

362
00:48:29,906 --> 00:48:31,433
And you are?

363
00:48:31,875 --> 00:48:33,538
My friend, Kawashima

364
00:48:33,944 --> 00:48:35,368
Huh...

365
00:48:35,946 --> 00:48:38,047
The grad student, Yoshizaki san

366
00:48:38,048 --> 00:48:39,416
Hello

367
00:49:00,871 --> 00:49:03,467
I forgot to give you my number

368
00:49:04,107 --> 00:49:05,074
Oh, right

369
00:49:05,075 --> 00:49:07,307
Call me, OK?

370
00:49:08,011 --> 00:49:09,011
Right

371
00:49:09,012 --> 00:49:10,539
Anytime, OK?

372
00:49:10,881 --> 00:49:12,014
Yeah

373
00:49:12,015 --> 00:49:13,474
Thank you

374
00:49:18,021 --> 00:49:23,359
"Everyone dies, therefore there's no
logical reason for ghosts not to exist..."

375
00:49:23,927 --> 00:49:28,526
"How many ghosts have..."

376
00:49:28,899 --> 00:49:32,360
"existed since prehistoric times..."

377
00:49:49,019 --> 00:49:51,285
Do you see it too?

378
00:49:53,090 --> 00:49:57,427
Sure you do, because it's really there

379
00:49:59,029 --> 00:50:02,331
Who is that?

380
00:50:03,033 --> 00:50:06,335
You'll have to catch him to find out

381
00:50:08,105 --> 00:50:11,339
Start right now, and you might succeed

382
00:50:15,078 --> 00:50:17,146
Have a go?

383
00:50:17,147 --> 00:50:19,048
What?

384
00:50:19,049 --> 00:50:22,351
Why don't you, right now

385
00:51:08,064 --> 00:51:09,932
He disappeared

386
00:51:09,933 --> 00:51:11,494
I see

387
00:51:14,004 --> 00:51:18,273
He must be a student... I don't know him

388
00:51:18,975 --> 00:51:23,244
Maybe you're right. Sorry I encouraged you

389
00:51:23,947 --> 00:51:25,371
See you

390
00:51:28,084 --> 00:51:30,316
wait a minute

391
00:51:34,024 --> 00:51:36,393
Just what was that?

392
00:51:54,044 --> 00:51:55,468
I'm cold...

393
00:52:12,095 --> 00:52:14,293
The spirit...

394
00:52:14,965 --> 00:52:18,133
Or consciousness, the soul,
whatever you want to call it,

395
00:52:18,134 --> 00:52:22,562
it turns out the realm they
inhabit has a finite capacity

396
00:52:24,107 --> 00:52:28,410
Whether that capacity accommodates billions
or trillions,

397
00:52:29,012 --> 00:52:31,472
eventually, it will run out of space

398
00:52:32,115 --> 00:52:36,151
Once it's filled to the brim,

399
00:52:36,152 --> 00:52:40,284
it's got to overflow somehow, somewhere

400
00:52:40,891 --> 00:52:42,418
But where?

401
00:52:44,961 --> 00:52:46,962
The souls have no choice

402
00:52:46,963 --> 00:52:50,458
but to ooze into another realm,
that is to say, our world

403
00:52:51,067 --> 00:52:54,460
Maybe, at first...

404
00:52:55,005 --> 00:52:58,307
it started with something really simple

405
00:53:19,963 --> 00:53:23,458
Once that realm reached critical mass,

406
00:53:23,967 --> 00:53:26,495
any device would have sufficed

407
00:53:27,137 --> 00:53:31,173
Thrown it together with the
means and materials at hand

408
00:53:31,174 --> 00:53:33,142
That's how I see it

409
00:53:33,143 --> 00:53:37,412
Excuse me, do you have any tape?

410
00:53:38,148 --> 00:53:41,484
Anything will do, some tape

411
00:53:42,986 --> 00:53:44,445
How's this?

412
00:53:45,055 --> 00:53:46,479
Thank you

413
00:54:17,087 --> 00:54:20,423
After many hours or days,

414
00:54:20,957 --> 00:54:24,555
or many weeks, it finally happens

415
00:55:15,111 --> 00:55:18,113
Through that process, it
spreads around the world

416
00:55:18,114 --> 00:55:22,474
But now they're no longer the
faint presence they began as

417
00:55:23,953 --> 00:55:26,322
You saw one yourself

418
00:55:30,093 --> 00:55:33,062
I don't believe your stories

419
00:55:33,063 --> 00:55:36,490
Right, sorry, it's all hypothetical

420
00:55:41,137 --> 00:55:43,005
Thanks for the tea

421
00:55:43,006 --> 00:55:44,073
Are you OK?

422
00:55:44,074 --> 00:55:46,306
Just fine

423
00:55:46,943 --> 00:55:49,111
But if this really happened,

424
00:55:49,112 --> 00:55:51,504
there's no turning back

425
00:55:52,982 --> 00:55:55,150
No matter how simple the device,

426
00:55:55,151 --> 00:56:00,122
once the system's complete,
it'll function on its own

427
00:56:00,123 --> 00:56:02,424
and become permanent

428
00:56:02,992 --> 00:56:04,451
In other words,

429
00:56:04,894 --> 00:56:08,355
the passage is now open...
that's how it looks

430
00:56:39,162 --> 00:56:41,997
Hello

431
00:56:41,998 --> 00:56:45,368
Oh, I see, our boss isn't there?

432
00:56:46,002 --> 00:56:48,103
Yes, I understand

433
00:56:48,104 --> 00:56:51,039
If he does stop by,

434
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:54,501
will you please ask him to call us?

435
00:56:55,879 --> 00:56:58,407
Yes, thank you very much

436
00:57:03,987 --> 00:57:05,514
Michi.

437
00:57:07,991 --> 00:57:10,451
What do you think is going on?

438
00:57:16,900 --> 00:57:19,428
Why's everyone disappearing?

439
00:57:35,084 --> 00:57:39,054
Oh, hello, this is Sunny
Plant Sales calling

440
00:57:39,055 --> 00:57:41,957
Thank you for your business

441
00:57:41,958 --> 00:57:46,295
Is our boss there with you by any chance?

442
00:57:47,130 --> 00:57:52,264
Oh, I see... Thank you, and excuse me

443
00:57:55,972 --> 00:57:57,533
I'll go look for him

444
00:57:58,007 --> 00:58:00,433
Wait, Junco, wait

445
00:58:06,082 --> 00:58:08,280
Yes. Hello...

446
00:58:11,955 --> 00:58:13,448
Boss?

447
00:58:14,157 --> 00:58:16,389
Help

448
00:58:17,927 --> 00:58:19,420
Yabe!

449
00:58:21,030 --> 00:58:23,262
Are you Yabe?

450
00:58:25,969 --> 00:58:27,462
Yabe!

451
00:58:37,046 --> 00:58:39,472
Help me...

452
00:58:50,994 --> 00:58:53,420
Help me...

453
00:58:55,965 --> 00:58:58,391
Help...

454
00:59:00,970 --> 00:59:03,396
Help...

455
00:59:23,126 --> 00:59:25,290
Junco...

456
00:59:27,030 --> 00:59:28,454
Junco!

457
01:00:03,967 --> 01:00:06,336
Junco, no!

458
01:00:09,906 --> 01:00:11,365
Junco!

459
01:00:15,111 --> 01:00:17,412
Are you OK?

460
01:00:18,114 --> 01:00:20,278
Are you OK?

461
01:00:45,908 --> 01:00:47,401
Junco

462
01:01:44,867 --> 01:01:46,394
Help me...

463
01:01:46,903 --> 01:01:48,396
Help me...

464
01:01:49,005 --> 01:01:50,498
Help me...

465
01:01:56,112 --> 01:01:58,146
Junco!

466
01:01:58,147 --> 01:02:01,449
Look, I'm right here

467
01:02:02,018 --> 01:02:05,411
I'm right here, it's OK

468
01:02:29,145 --> 01:02:31,343
Excuse me

469
01:03:02,145 --> 01:03:05,538
Karasawa Harue
tel: 090 -4079 -2677

470
01:05:48,911 --> 01:05:52,281
What are you doing, Harue!

471
01:05:53,916 --> 01:05:56,342
You're dripping wet!

472
01:05:56,886 --> 01:05:58,515
They went away...

473
01:05:59,155 --> 01:06:01,990
They've all disappeared...
They always do...

474
01:06:01,991 --> 01:06:03,484
I have to run away...

475
01:06:04,093 --> 01:06:06,257
Run away somewhere...

476
01:06:09,065 --> 01:06:10,455
Harue!

477
01:06:11,934 --> 01:06:13,393
Hey. Harue!

478
01:06:13,936 --> 01:06:15,463
Listen, Harue!

479
01:06:16,005 --> 01:06:17,464
Harue!

480
01:06:17,907 --> 01:06:20,401
Calm down! Harue!

481
01:06:41,897 --> 01:06:43,356
Thank you...

482
01:07:13,162 --> 01:07:17,522
I always wondered what it's like to die...

483
01:07:17,967 --> 01:07:20,529
From when I was really little...

484
01:07:22,872 --> 01:07:24,467
I was always alone

485
01:07:25,141 --> 01:07:27,476
Any parents or family?

486
01:07:28,010 --> 01:07:31,346
Sure, but they're irrelevant

487
01:07:32,114 --> 01:07:34,278
Right...

488
01:07:37,119 --> 01:07:39,154
That after death,

489
01:07:39,155 --> 01:07:42,991
you live happily with everyone over there

490
01:07:42,992 --> 01:07:45,160
Can we stop talking about this?

491
01:07:45,161 --> 01:07:47,462
But it may be true

492
01:07:48,164 --> 01:07:51,295
Sure, but...

493
01:07:52,168 --> 01:07:55,470
Then in high school it dawned on me

494
01:07:57,973 --> 01:08:01,309
you might be all alone after death, too

495
01:08:04,880 --> 01:08:07,015
There's no way to know

496
01:08:07,016 --> 01:08:09,083
How could you?

497
01:08:09,084 --> 01:08:12,477
The idea was so terrifying

498
01:08:13,923 --> 01:08:16,383
I couldn't even bear it

499
01:08:17,993 --> 01:08:20,061
That nothing changes with death,

500
01:08:20,062 --> 01:08:23,296
just right now, forever

501
01:08:29,038 --> 01:08:33,307
Is that what becoming a ghost is about?

502
01:08:33,876 --> 01:08:38,012
You can't mess with that. It's really bad

503
01:08:38,013 --> 01:08:41,542
What have ghosts got to do with us?

504
01:08:41,884 --> 01:08:43,547
Besides, we're alive

505
01:08:46,021 --> 01:08:48,515
Then, who are they?

506
01:08:56,899 --> 01:08:59,461
Are they really alive?

507
01:09:01,971 --> 01:09:04,397
How are they different from ghosts?

508
01:09:13,115 --> 01:09:15,313
In fact,

509
01:09:15,985 --> 01:09:18,445
ghosts and people are the same,

510
01:09:19,889 --> 01:09:22,417
whether they're dead or alive

511
01:09:26,161 --> 01:09:29,554
It's not right. It's wrong

512
01:09:29,999 --> 01:09:32,368
They're all crazy

513
01:09:34,904 --> 01:09:37,972
Nobody knows what happens when you die

514
01:09:37,973 --> 01:09:42,435
All this about ghosts, but I won't
believe in them, even if I see one

515
01:09:42,945 --> 01:09:44,472
But I do know,

516
01:09:45,114 --> 01:09:50,084
that I'm definitely alive and so are you,
Harue

517
01:09:50,085 --> 01:09:52,454
That's for sure, right?

518
01:09:53,155 --> 01:09:58,425
So I don't want to think about
the fact we'll die someday

519
01:10:00,930 --> 01:10:02,389
Just maybe...

520
01:10:02,865 --> 01:10:06,100
In 10 years, or at least
while we're still alive,

521
01:10:06,101 --> 01:10:09,037
they'll invent a drug that prevents death

522
01:10:09,038 --> 01:10:12,465
Then, we could live forever and ever

523
01:10:13,075 --> 01:10:17,435
Of course you might think I'm
crazy to say that, but...

524
01:10:17,947 --> 01:10:20,316
I'd rather bet on that

525
01:10:21,984 --> 01:10:24,376
You want to live forever?

526
01:10:24,887 --> 01:10:26,311
Yeah

527
01:10:27,022 --> 01:10:29,090
That sounds like fun?

528
01:10:29,091 --> 01:10:32,359
Yeah... That's what I think

529
01:10:38,133 --> 01:10:43,335
Huh... Maybe I've got it all wrong

530
01:10:47,176 --> 01:10:49,306
No...

531
01:10:50,012 --> 01:10:55,282
It'll turn out just like you say

532
01:10:57,152 --> 01:10:59,316
I'm sure

533
01:10:59,922 --> 01:11:01,346
What?

534
01:11:04,093 --> 01:11:07,395
Ghosts won't kill people

535
01:11:08,998 --> 01:11:12,300
Because that would just make more ghosts

536
01:11:14,036 --> 01:11:15,529
Isn't that right?

537
01:11:19,108 --> 01:11:23,309
Instead, they'll try to
make people immortal

538
01:11:26,982 --> 01:11:29,317
By quietly...

539
01:11:31,887 --> 01:11:34,381
trapping them in their own loneliness

540
01:11:43,098 --> 01:11:45,524
Help...

541
01:11:47,970 --> 01:11:50,362
Help...

542
01:12:54,136 --> 01:12:57,472
Junco, it'll be OK

543
01:12:58,073 --> 01:13:00,408
It'll be OK

544
01:13:00,976 --> 01:13:02,503
OK...

545
01:13:21,864 --> 01:13:23,425
I fell asleep...

546
01:13:27,970 --> 01:13:29,497
How do you feel?

547
01:13:29,938 --> 01:13:31,362
Yeah

548
01:13:32,107 --> 01:13:35,477
Something to drink? How about some coffee?

549
01:13:49,057 --> 01:13:50,425
Michi...

550
01:13:51,026 --> 01:13:52,450
What?

551
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:57,492
Am I just going to die like this?

552
01:13:59,902 --> 01:14:01,531
Of course not

553
01:14:03,172 --> 01:14:05,438
That's right...

554
01:14:06,008 --> 01:14:08,502
I'll just keep on living, all alone...

555
01:14:31,166 --> 01:14:33,167
What?

556
01:14:33,168 --> 01:14:35,298
No

557
01:15:08,937 --> 01:15:10,396
Junco!

558
01:15:11,907 --> 01:15:13,366
Junco

559
01:15:14,877 --> 01:15:16,336
Junco!

560
01:15:31,960 --> 01:15:33,487
Junco!

561
01:15:38,901 --> 01:15:40,496
Why! Why!

562
01:15:49,912 --> 01:15:52,440
Junco, don't go!

563
01:15:53,015 --> 01:15:55,247
Junco

564
01:16:44,933 --> 01:16:46,392
Mother?

565
01:16:50,072 --> 01:16:52,270
Mother?

566
01:16:54,910 --> 01:16:56,369
Mother!

567
01:17:01,950 --> 01:17:03,511
I'll be right there

568
01:19:38,974 --> 01:19:40,398
Harue...

569
01:19:44,913 --> 01:19:46,474
Harue! Hey...

570
01:19:51,086 --> 01:19:55,321
Kawashima... take me with you

571
01:19:59,895 --> 01:20:02,287
I'm scared to be alone

572
01:20:07,936 --> 01:20:09,531
Take me somewhere

573
01:20:22,017 --> 01:20:25,251
OK, sure

574
01:20:26,922 --> 01:20:27,922
Where to?

575
01:20:27,923 --> 01:20:29,484
Somewhere far away

576
01:20:31,159 --> 01:20:32,993
Out of Order

577
01:20:32,994 --> 01:20:35,454
Shit, let's just go!

578
01:21:15,136 --> 01:21:17,368
There's no one...

579
01:21:20,041 --> 01:21:21,465
No...

580
01:21:28,016 --> 01:21:30,385
Where did everyone go?

581
01:21:34,956 --> 01:21:36,483
I'm here

582
01:21:41,162 --> 01:21:43,531
I'm here beside you

583
01:21:48,937 --> 01:21:50,396
Even if,

584
01:21:51,072 --> 01:21:54,533
there's no one else, it doesn't matter

585
01:21:55,944 --> 01:22:00,304
We are both definitely here

586
01:22:08,056 --> 01:22:10,322
Guess that's true...

587
01:22:41,156 --> 01:22:43,320
What happened!

588
01:22:48,163 --> 01:22:50,030
I've got to go back!

589
01:22:50,031 --> 01:22:53,133
What? No! We've come this far!

590
01:22:53,134 --> 01:22:56,003
But this is the end of the line

591
01:22:56,004 --> 01:22:59,039
That's not true. It'll start moving

592
01:22:59,040 --> 01:23:02,342
I'll go check with the driver. Come with me

593
01:23:03,878 --> 01:23:06,080
OK, but promise you'll wait right here

594
01:23:06,081 --> 01:23:08,473
I'll be right back. Promise

595
01:23:46,121 --> 01:23:48,285
Harue!

596
01:24:56,891 --> 01:24:58,486
The Forbidden Room

597
01:26:06,027 --> 01:26:08,419
Construction Materials -red tape

598
01:27:59,974 --> 01:28:01,433
I'm...

599
01:28:05,013 --> 01:28:07,314
Not alone...

600
01:28:26,134 --> 01:28:27,968
Harue.

601
01:28:27,969 --> 01:28:30,361
It's me, Kawashima

602
01:28:33,174 --> 01:28:35,509
Harue! Listen!

603
01:28:38,112 --> 01:28:41,482
Listen, what do you say to this...

604
01:28:42,016 --> 01:28:44,476
The two of us live together

605
01:28:44,886 --> 01:28:47,517
That way, we can always be together

606
01:28:48,923 --> 01:28:51,519
If we keep living alone,

607
01:28:51,926 --> 01:28:55,455
we'll just get worse and worse because
we're weak

608
01:28:55,897 --> 01:28:58,131
We'll balance each other out

609
01:28:58,132 --> 01:29:00,501
How about living that way?

610
01:29:01,069 --> 01:29:03,103
Would you try it with me?

611
01:29:03,104 --> 01:29:06,497
What do you think, Harue! Listen!

612
01:29:15,950 --> 01:29:17,249
Harue!

613
01:29:18,019 --> 01:29:19,443
Harue!

614
01:29:20,988 --> 01:29:22,412
Harue!

