Kanagawa: Missing
Hirayama Michio, age 80

618
01:29:42,176 --> 01:29:46,479
Kanagawa: Missing
Kawahara Takumi, age 25

619
01:29:46,981 --> 01:29:50,442
Saitama: Missing
Tomioka Shigeki, age 8

620
01:29:50,885 --> 01:29:54,449
Tokyo: Missing
Yoshida Tomoko, age 21

621
01:29:54,889 --> 01:29:58,091
Tokyo: Missing
Nakajima Kumi, age 5

622
01:29:58,092 --> 01:30:01,462
Kanagawa: Missing
Kitaoka Eri, age 3

623
01:30:02,063 --> 01:30:05,524
Tokyo: Missing
Fukuda Tatsuya, age 57

624
01:30:54,081 --> 01:30:57,246
Um... are you OK?

625
01:31:03,057 --> 01:31:04,516
Breakdown?

626
01:31:07,028 --> 01:31:08,094
Yeah

627
01:31:08,095 --> 01:31:09,519
Want some?

628
01:31:20,041 --> 01:31:21,409
You are?

629
01:31:22,043 --> 01:31:24,503
Oh, me? Um...

630
01:31:26,981 --> 01:31:28,440
What are you doing here?

631
01:31:31,919 --> 01:31:34,288
What am I doing here...

632
01:31:36,123 --> 01:31:37,422
You?

633
01:31:45,032 --> 01:31:48,101
So neither your dad nor your mom

634
01:31:48,102 --> 01:31:50,403
made it through...

635
01:31:50,905 --> 01:31:52,329
No...

636
01:31:53,040 --> 01:31:56,109
So many things happened at once,

637
01:31:56,110 --> 01:31:59,446
it's impossible to sort them all out

638
01:32:00,014 --> 01:32:01,404
Yeah

639
01:32:04,151 --> 01:32:08,386
Me too. My head's all messed up

640
01:32:09,023 --> 01:32:12,518
So you're a student, Kawashima?

641
01:32:12,894 --> 01:32:14,284
Yeah

642
01:32:14,996 --> 01:32:16,062
Lucky you

643
01:32:16,063 --> 01:32:18,064
I don't think so

644
01:32:18,065 --> 01:32:19,065
Here

645
01:32:19,066 --> 01:32:21,401
Oh, thanks...

646
01:32:24,171 --> 01:32:26,106
And you?

647
01:32:26,107 --> 01:32:28,041
I had a job

648
01:32:28,042 --> 01:32:30,043
Wow, amazing

649
01:32:30,044 --> 01:32:32,276
Nothing amazing

650
01:32:34,882 --> 01:32:37,376
Did you have any friends?

651
01:32:37,952 --> 01:32:39,376
Friends?

652
01:32:42,023 --> 01:32:44,124
Maybe one, I guess

653
01:32:44,125 --> 01:32:46,357
What was she like?

654
01:32:49,130 --> 01:32:51,465
What? I don't really know...

655
01:32:53,100 --> 01:32:56,036
I never really found out...

656
01:32:56,037 --> 01:32:58,303
Where is she?

657
01:32:58,873 --> 01:33:00,366
Somewhere...

658
01:33:03,044 --> 01:33:05,413
OK, try starting it

659
01:33:16,924 --> 01:33:18,519
OK, good

660
01:33:36,043 --> 01:33:38,044
Why don't you look for her?

661
01:33:38,045 --> 01:33:39,435
What?

662
01:33:40,114 --> 01:33:44,474
She's still somewhere, right? You've got to
help her then

663
01:33:46,120 --> 01:33:48,250
But...

664
01:33:48,956 --> 01:33:52,349
Let's go find her. I'll help you

665
01:33:58,165 --> 01:34:01,433
This is the last stop...

666
01:34:06,040 --> 01:34:09,433
After that we go as far as we can

667
01:34:14,081 --> 01:34:17,508
I can sort of see...

668
01:34:18,919 --> 01:34:20,287
The future...

669
01:34:30,097 --> 01:34:34,264
"Help"

670
01:34:57,158 --> 01:34:59,390
Look over there

671
01:35:02,129 --> 01:35:04,498
An abandoned factory?

672
01:35:11,105 --> 01:35:13,337
I wonder...

673
01:35:16,010 --> 01:35:17,503
Shall we try it?

674
01:35:36,063 --> 01:35:39,933
Listen, even if you see a door sealed with
red tape,

675
01:35:39,934 --> 01:35:42,496
don't go near it, OK?

676
01:35:43,003 --> 01:35:44,462
I know

677
01:36:08,963 --> 01:36:10,353
You OK?

678
01:36:48,102 --> 01:36:51,370
Look... at this

679
01:37:01,148 --> 01:37:03,449
Look... over there

680
01:37:30,010 --> 01:37:31,144
Kawashima

681
01:37:31,145 --> 01:37:33,046
Harue!

682
01:37:33,047 --> 01:37:34,506
Watch out!

683
01:37:36,917 --> 01:37:38,546
What happened, Harue!

684
01:37:39,053 --> 01:37:42,252
What are you doing with that?

685
01:37:45,926 --> 01:37:49,558
Let's get out of this place, together

686
01:37:52,032 --> 01:37:53,559
Together?

687
01:37:54,168 --> 01:37:56,298
Yeah

688
01:38:08,882 --> 01:38:10,116
Come on, hand it over

689
01:38:10,117 --> 01:38:12,383
Harue! Harue!

690
01:38:16,056 --> 01:38:18,516
Oh, no, a hospital...

691
01:38:31,071 --> 01:38:33,531
Harue! Don't die!

692
01:38:33,974 --> 01:38:36,343
Come on! Please!

693
01:38:37,878 --> 01:38:39,302
Help me!

694
01:38:41,982 --> 01:38:43,372
Harue!

695
01:38:56,964 --> 01:38:59,333
We couldn't save her...

696
01:39:01,068 --> 01:39:02,492
No...

697
01:39:26,126 --> 01:39:28,461
We're out of gas...

698
01:39:29,963 --> 01:39:32,525
I'll get some, there was gas back there

699
01:39:32,933 --> 01:39:34,392
You'll be OK?

700
01:39:34,968 --> 01:39:37,303
Wait for me. I'll be OK

701
01:41:34,021 --> 01:41:36,253
Forever...

702
01:41:38,025 --> 01:41:40,059
Death was...

703
01:41:40,060 --> 01:41:43,396
Eternal loneliness...

704
01:41:51,872 --> 01:41:53,399
Help

705
01:41:54,107 --> 01:41:56,373
Help

706
01:41:56,977 --> 01:41:58,538
Help

707
01:41:58,946 --> 01:42:03,249
Don't ask me!
What's that got to do with me!

708
01:42:04,051 --> 01:42:06,152
Forever...

709
01:42:06,153 --> 01:42:08,454
Death was...

710
01:42:09,089 --> 01:42:11,355
Eternal loneliness...

711
01:42:18,932 --> 01:42:21,267
You're not real

712
01:42:22,069 --> 01:42:25,462
I refuse to acknowledge...
Never...

713
01:42:26,039 --> 01:42:28,465
I refuse to acknowledge death!

714
01:43:13,020 --> 01:43:14,513
I know

715
01:43:16,023 --> 01:43:18,358
I'll catch you

716
01:43:18,926 --> 01:43:21,352
Then you'll disappear

717
01:43:22,095 --> 01:43:25,294
That's it, right! Right!

718
01:43:25,933 --> 01:43:28,427
You can't beat me!

719
01:43:57,097 --> 01:43:59,363
I am...

720
01:44:01,935 --> 01:44:04,395
Real...

721
01:45:58,952 --> 01:46:00,445
Kawashima!

722
01:46:07,894 --> 01:46:08,994
What is it?

723
01:46:08,995 --> 01:46:11,523
Forget it... Let's go...

724
01:48:26,967 --> 01:48:29,302
It's too much...

725
01:48:40,981 --> 01:48:44,510
What... Are you doing?

726
01:48:50,891 --> 01:48:54,420
You went in there...

727
01:48:55,996 --> 01:48:57,420
Me?

728
01:48:59,032 --> 01:49:01,492
Yeah, I did. But I'm fine

729
01:49:16,182 --> 01:49:18,448
Don't cry

730
01:49:41,942 --> 01:49:43,503
You want to go back?

731
01:49:44,911 --> 01:49:47,280
To what's left of Harue?

732
01:49:52,886 --> 01:49:55,278
That make you feel better?

733
01:50:00,060 --> 01:50:04,329
If that's what you want, I'll go with you

734
01:50:07,133 --> 01:50:09,297
No...

735
01:50:10,036 --> 01:50:11,529
Let's go...

736
01:50:12,105 --> 01:50:14,474
As far as we can go

737
01:50:19,012 --> 01:50:21,381
Are you sure about that?

738
01:50:27,120 --> 01:50:28,544
Yeah

739
01:50:47,040 --> 01:50:48,499
Can you get out?

740
01:50:56,016 --> 01:50:57,406
You OK?

741
01:51:10,030 --> 01:51:11,489
Be careful

742
01:51:22,108 --> 01:51:24,340
Wait here. OK?

743
01:52:38,918 --> 01:52:42,413
Death comes to us all...

744
01:52:42,989 --> 01:52:46,959
If so, maybe we would have been happier,

745
01:52:46,960 --> 01:52:49,488
had we gone with the rest

746
01:52:50,029 --> 01:52:53,490
But we chose to keep going

747
01:52:54,000 --> 01:52:56,562
into the future...

748
01:53:15,922 --> 01:53:18,157
We'll head for Latin America

749
01:53:18,158 --> 01:53:21,528
We're still getting signals there

750
01:53:22,061 --> 01:53:24,453
Though they're pretty weak

751
01:53:25,165 --> 01:53:28,262
We've got to give it a try,

752
01:53:28,935 --> 01:53:31,304
no matter what we find

753
01:53:33,973 --> 01:53:37,142
If anyone's survived,

754
01:53:37,143 --> 01:53:39,512
we can head out again

755
01:53:41,981 --> 01:53:44,350
and go as far as we can

756
01:53:52,892 --> 01:53:56,262
Come on, be strong

757
01:53:59,999 --> 01:54:03,460
Have I done the right thing?

758
01:54:05,138 --> 01:54:07,268
Yes

759
01:54:07,874 --> 01:54:09,141
Are you sure?

760
01:54:09,142 --> 01:54:11,009
Yes

761
01:54:11,010 --> 01:54:14,312
You're doing the right thing

762
01:54:51,084 --> 01:54:55,387
Now, alone with my last
friend in the world,

763
01:54:56,089 --> 01:54:59,288
I have found happiness

